cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AR 

The paper discusses the parallelization of deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks, on a parallel computing system. This topic falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Architecture (cs.AR). Given the focus on parallel computing and deep learning, cs.DC and cs.LG are the most likely categories. However, the use of convolutional neural networks and the evaluation on image datasets suggest cs.CV as a likely category as well. The use of neural networks also makes cs.NE a possible category, while the focus on optimizing performance for a specific computing system suggests cs.AR as a less likely but still possible category.
